<@U33EGB4TX> i just reviewed your article.

1. well written
2. same feedback I gave <@U340CHVJA> : add a blurb at the top of the article (in italics perhaps) that says “This article is part of a series in which, …”. You can still have a bit of introduction at the beginning since it’s the first article, but we want to have that consistent blurb at the top of each article
3. When we mention “Elves” (paragraph 4), let’s link to EDHREC’s elves page.
4. missing period end of paragraph 4
5. I’d like to tie in EDHREC some without it being too cheesy. Can you talk about how you used EDHREC to find cards? For example, you can mention something simple like “Although XYZ card is used somewhere near 80% of the time with Ezuri, …”.
6. we are having images link to their edhrec pages, right?
7. Can we get the decklist displayed here as well as the tappedout link? I think we did this for <@U340CHVJA>’s article.
So, if you go to my article, which appears to be published btw (not my doing), there is still just a link to deckbox. Jason said he was still working on it.

i’m working on an article on commander diversity, which is basically measuring how much decks for a particular commander change. I measure the “average number of cards in common across decks"
